    Barcode abundance comparison

    compareAbundance.Rd

    Takes a dataframe of barcode counts, computes the mean abundance of each barcode for two specific conditions, then do a line plot for both conditions

    Usage

    compareAbundance(counts, condition, condition_names)

    Arguments

    counts

    dataframe containing raw counts of barcodes

    condition

    sample condition of interest

    condition_names

    names of possible conditions in experiment

    Value

    Returns a text file

    Details

    compareAbundance

    Compare barcode abundance between 2 conditions using EdgeR

    Examples

    data(test.dge)
compareAbundance(test.dge, test.dge$samples$group, c("T0","T0b"))
